build:
run make on any unix-like system. You will be prompted during the build process.

run:
MJPP is a helper shell script I use to "launch" the program with the correct classpath
you can also do

java -classpath ".:/path/2/javacup" MiniJavaPrettyPrinter

lastly, the test files I used are in tests/

I have included everything for sake of correctness.

COOL THING:
if you don't supply command-line options, you can use stdin
